    "technology_id": 1,
    "module_id": 5,
    "slug": "structured-and-nested-lists",
    "title": "Structured and Nested Lists",
    "description": "HTML ul, ol, and dl elements group related content with semantic meaning and accessibility support.",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 1,
        "text": "HTML List Types and When to Use Each"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "HTML provides three native list elements to group related content semantically. "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ul>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ul"
          },
          {
            "value": " creates an "
          },
          {
            "value": "unordered list",
            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "value": " where sequence does not matter, rendered with bullet markers by default. "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ol>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ol"
          },
          {
            "value": " creates an "
          },
          {
            "value": "ordered list",
            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "value": " where sequence is meaningful, rendered with numbers or letters. "
          },
          {
            "value": "<dl>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dl"
          },
          {
            "value": " creates a "
          },
          {
            "value": "description list",
            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "value": " pairing terms with their definitions or metadata. All three expose their structure to assistive technologies through "
          },
          {
            "value": "ARIA list roles",
            "bold": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/list_role"
          },
          {
            "value": ", allowing screen readers to announce item counts and navigate by list item."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "headers": [
          "Element",
          "Child Elements",
          "Use Case",
          "Screen Reader Announcement"
        ],
        "rows": [
          [
            "<ul>",
            "<li>",
            "Items with no meaningful order: features, links, ingredients",
            "\"list, N items\""
          ],
          [
            "<ol>",
            "<li>",
            "Steps, rankings, instructions where order matters",
            "\"list, N items\" with position"
          ],
          [
            "<dl>",
            "<dt> + <dd>",
            "Term-definition pairs, metadata, glossaries, FAQs",
            "Varies by screen reader"
          ],
          [
            "Nested list",
            "<ul> or <ol> inside <li>",
            "Hierarchical content: outlines, subcategories, submenus",
            "\"list, N items\" per level"
          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "callout",
        "variant": "info",
        "title": "Lists Communicate Grouping to Assistive Technologies",
        "text": "Screen readers announce the number of items in a list before reading them, giving users a mental map of the content. Using divs with bullet-point characters instead of real list elements removes this announcement entirely."
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "title": "All Three List Types Side by Side",
        "description": "Demonstrates ul, ol, and dl in a single page, showing the correct child elements for each type and the situations each list type is best suited for.",
        "code_snippet": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n    <title>HTML List Types</title>\n    <style>\n      body { font-family: sans-serif; padding: 2rem; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }\n      h2 { color: #1a1a2e; border-bottom: 2px solid #eee; padding-bottom: 0.4rem; }\n      dl { display: grid; grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr; gap: 0.25rem 1.5rem; }\n      dt { font-weight: bold; color: #0077cc; }\n      dd { margin: 0; color: #333; }\n    </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n\n    <!-- ul: order of features does not matter -->\n    <h2>Key Features</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Responsive design out of the box</li>\n      <li>Built-in dark mode support</li>\n      <li>Zero runtime dependencies</li>\n      <li>Accessible by default</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <!-- ol: steps must be followed in this exact order -->\n    <h2>Getting Started</h2>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Install the package with <code>npm install acme-ui</code></li>\n      <li>Import the stylesheet into your entry file</li>\n      <li>Wrap your app in the ThemeProvider component</li>\n      <li>Use components directly from the package</li>\n    </ol>\n\n    <!-- dl: term-definition pairs for a glossary or metadata block -->\n    <h2>Glossary</h2>\n    <dl>\n      <dt>Accessibility</dt>\n      <dd>The practice of designing products usable by people with disabilities.</dd>\n\n      <dt>Semantic HTML</dt>\n      <dd>Using HTML elements that convey meaning about their content to browsers and assistive tools.</dd>\n\n      <dt>ARIA</dt>\n      <dd>Accessible Rich Internet Applications, a set of attributes that extend HTML semantics.</dd>\n    </dl>\n\n  </body>\n</html>",
        "output": "The page shows three sections. The first is a bulleted list of four features. The second is a numbered list of four setup steps. The third is a two-column glossary layout with bold blue terms on the left and their definitions on the right. Screen readers announce 'list, 4 items' before each list and read each term and description pair in the glossary sequentially.",
        "images": null,
        "video_url": null
      },
      {
        "title": "WRONG vs RIGHT: Fake Lists vs Semantic Lists",
        "description": "Contrasts using paragraphs and manual bullet characters against real list elements, showing what screen readers miss when fake lists are used.",
        "code_snippet": "<!-- WRONG: manual bullet characters in paragraphs -->\n<!-- Screen readers read these as plain paragraphs with no list structure -->\n<!-- Users do not hear item counts or list navigation shortcuts -->\n<p>• Responsive design out of the box</p>\n<p>• Built-in dark mode support</p>\n<p>• Zero runtime dependencies</p>\n\n<!-- WRONG: div-based fake ordered list -->\n<div>1. Install the package</div>\n<div>2. Import the stylesheet</div>\n<div>3. Wrap your app</div>\n<!-- Screen readers announce three separate generic elements, not a 3-item list -->\n\n\n<!-- RIGHT: semantic ul for unordered items -->\n<!-- Screen reader: \"list, 3 items\" then reads each item -->\n<ul>\n  <li>Responsive design out of the box</li>\n  <li>Built-in dark mode support</li>\n  <li>Zero runtime dependencies</li>\n</ul>\n\n<!-- RIGHT: semantic ol for sequential steps -->\n<!-- Screen reader: \"list, 3 items\" with step position for each item -->\n<ol>\n  <li>Install the package</li>\n  <li>Import the stylesheet</li>\n  <li>Wrap your app</li>\n</ol>",
        "output": "The WRONG versions display visually similar to the RIGHT versions but lose all list semantics. Screen readers reading the WRONG versions announce three separate paragraph or generic elements with no item count, no list navigation, and no positional context. The RIGHT versions trigger list announcements, allow screen reader users to jump between items with keyboard shortcuts, and report the total item count before reading.",
        "images": null,
        "video_url": null
      },
      {
        "title": "ol with type and start Attributes",
        "description": "Shows how the type and start attributes on ol control the marker style and starting number, useful for multi-part documents, legal numbering, and resuming lists after interrupting content.",
        "code_snippet": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n    <title>Ordered List Attributes</title>\n    <style>\n      body { font-family: sans-serif; padding: 2rem; max-width: 600px; }\n      h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }\n    </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n\n    <h3>Alphabetical list (type=\"a\")</h3>\n    <!-- type=\"a\" uses lowercase letters as markers -->\n    <ol type=\"a\">\n      <li>Define the problem statement</li>\n      <li>Research existing solutions</li>\n      <li>Prototype and test</li>\n    </ol>\n\n    <h3>Uppercase Roman numerals (type=\"I\")</h3>\n    <!-- type=\"I\" uses uppercase Roman numerals -->\n    <ol type=\"I\">\n      <li>Introduction</li>\n      <li>Methodology</li>\n      <li>Results</li>\n    </ol>\n\n    <h3>Continuing from item 4 (start=\"4\")</h3>\n    <!-- start=\"4\" resumes numbering after a break in the document -->\n    <!-- Use this when content interrupts a continuous list -->\n    <ol start=\"4\">\n      <li>Deploy to staging environment</li>\n      <li>Run end-to-end tests</li>\n      <li>Promote to production</li>\n    </ol>\n\n    <h3>Reversed countdown (reversed)</h3>\n    <!-- reversed counts down from the total to 1 -->\n    <ol reversed>\n      <li>Gold medal: Team Alpha</li>\n      <li>Silver medal: Team Beta</li>\n      <li>Bronze medal: Team Gamma</li>\n    </ol>\n\n  </body>\n</html>",
        "output": "The page shows four ordered lists: the first uses a, b, c markers; the second uses I, II, III Roman numerals; the third starts at number 4 and counts 4, 5, 6; the fourth counts down as 3, 2, 1 for the reversed ranking. All are read by screen readers as standard ordered lists with the correct positional context for each item.",
        "images": null,
        "video_url": null
      }
    ],
    "image_banner_url": null,
    "images": null,
    "video_url": null,
    "when_to_use": [
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Use "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ul>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ul"
          },
          {
            "value": " when listing items where changing the order would not affect the meaning, such as features, ingredients, or navigation links."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Use "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ol>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ol"
          },
          {
            "value": " when sequence is essential, such as installation steps, ranked results, legal clauses, or recipe instructions where order changes the outcome."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Use "
          },
          {
            "value": "<dl>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dl"
          },
          {
            "value": " when presenting term-value pairs such as glossaries, metadata blocks, FAQs, or product specification tables with label and value relationships."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      }
    ],
    "when_to_avoid": [
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Avoid using "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ol>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ol"
          },
          {
            "value": " when the numbers are for visual decoration only and the items have no meaningful sequence, as this misrepresents the content structure to assistive technologies."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Avoid placing block-level elements like "
          },
          {
            "value": "<p>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/p"
          },
          {
            "value": " or "
          },
          {
            "value": "<div>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/div"
          },
          {
            "value": " as direct children of "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ul>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ul"
          },
          {
            "value": " or "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ol>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ol"
          },
          {
            "value": ". Only "
          },
          {
            "value": "<li>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/li"
          },
          {
            "value": " is a valid direct child."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Avoid using "
          },
          {
            "value": "<dl>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dl"
          },
          {
            "value": " for content that is not genuinely a term-description relationship. For simple grouped content, "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ul>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ul"
          },
          {
            "value": " or "
          },
          {
            "value": "<table>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/table"
          },
          {
            "value": " is more appropriate."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      }
    ],
    "what_it_solves": [
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Using plain "
          },
          {
            "value": "<p>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/p"
          },
          {
            "value": " tags with manual bullet characters removes the "
          },
          {
            "value": "ARIA list role",
            "bold": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/list_role"
          },
          {
            "value": ", so screen readers cannot announce item counts or enable list navigation shortcuts."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Without "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ol>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ol"
          },
          {
            "value": ", sequential steps rendered as plain text give no positional context, making it easy for users to lose their place in multi-step instructions."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Without "
          },
          {
            "value": "<dl>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dl"
          },
          {
            "value": ", term-value pairs formatted as two-column "
          },
          {
            "value": "<div>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/div"
          },
          {
            "value": " grids have no machine-readable association between a term and its description."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      }
    ],
    "conceptual_understanding": [
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "A "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ul>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ul"
          },
          {
            "value": " is like a shopping bag: you toss items in and the order you pull them out does not matter. A "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ol>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ol"
          },
          {
            "value": " is like a recipe: you must follow the steps in sequence or the dish fails. The element you choose tells both humans and machines which situation they are in."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "A "
          },
          {
            "value": "<dl>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dl"
          },
          {
            "value": " is like a dictionary page: each entry has a bold headword ("
          },
          {
            "value": "<dt>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dt"
          },
          {
            "value": ") followed by its definition ("
          },
          {
            "value": "<dd>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dd"
          },
          {
            "value": "). The pairing is not just visual, it is a machine-readable relationship that assistive technologies can traverse and expose to users."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "The "
          },
          {
            "value": "ARIA list role",
            "bold": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/list_role"
          },
          {
            "value": " exposed by "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ul>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ul"
          },
          {
            "value": " and "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ol>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ol"
          },
          {
            "value": " is like the chapter counter in an audiobook player. Before reading a chapter the player tells you 'chapter 3 of 12', giving you a mental map of where you are. Without list semantics, every item is read as an isolated sentence with no map."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      }
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Placing non-"
          },
          {
            "value": "<li>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/li"
          },
          {
            "value": " children in "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ul>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ul"
          },
          {
            "value": " or "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ol>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ol"
          },
          {
            "value": ": invalid HTML that browsers silently fix but that breaks the list item count for screen readers."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Using "
          },
          {
            "value": "<br>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/br"
          },
          {
            "value": " to fake list items: line breaks inside a single "
          },
          {
            "value": "<p>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/p"
          },
          {
            "value": " produce no list role, no item count, and no keyboard navigation for screen reader users."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Using "
          },
          {
            "value": "<dt>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dt"
          },
          {
            "value": " without a following "
          },
          {
            "value": "<dd>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dd"
          },
          {
            "value": ": an orphaned term in a "
          },
          {
            "value": "<dl>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dl"
          },
          {
            "value": " breaks the term-description pairing that assistive technologies depend on."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      }
    ],
    "bonus_tips": [
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "In CSS, use "
          },
          {
            "value": "list-style: none",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/list-style"
          },
          {
            "value": " to remove bullet markers from a "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ul>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ul"
          },
          {
            "value": " used for navigation, but note that Safari removes the "
          },
          {
            "value": "ARIA list role",
            "bold": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/list_role"
          },
          {
            "value": " when this style is applied. Add "
          },
          {
            "value": "role=\"list\"",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/list_role"
          },
          {
            "value": " explicitly to the "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ul>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true
          },
          {
            "value": " to restore the semantic role in Safari."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Use the "
          },
          {
            "value": "value",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/li#value"
          },
          {
            "value": " attribute on individual "
          },
          {
            "value": "<li>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/li"
          },
          {
            "value": " elements inside an "
          },
          {
            "value": "<ol>",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ol"
          },
          {
            "value": " to override the counter for a specific item, with all subsequent items continuing from that new value automatically."
          }
        ],
        "type": "paragraph"
      }
    ],
